          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-1" n="1">D<hi rend="small-caps">EAR </hi>S<hi rend="small-caps">IR</hi>, Since you in humble wise</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-2" n="2">Have made a recantation,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-3" n="3">From your low bended knees arise;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-4" n="4">I hate such poor prostration.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-5" n="5"><lb/>'Tis bravery that moves the brave,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-6" n="6">As one nail drives another;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-7" n="7">If you from me would mercy have,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-8" n="8">Pray, Sir, be such another.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-9" n="9"><lb/>You that so long maintain'd the field</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-10" n="10">With true poetic vigour;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-11" n="11">Now you lay down your pen and yield,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-12" n="12">You make a wretched figure.<note place="foot">·A leg awry.</note></l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-13" n="13"><lb/>Submit, but do't with sword in hand,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-14" n="14">And write a panegyric</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-15" n="15">Upon the man you cannot stand;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-16" n="16">I'll have it done in lyric:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-17" n="17"><lb/>That all the boys I teach may sing</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-18" n="18">The achievements of their Chiron;<note place="foot">·A fair open for you.</note></l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-19" n="19">What conquests my stern looks can bring,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-20" n="20">Without the help of iron.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-21" n="21"><lb/>A small goose-quill, ycelp'd a pen,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-22" n="22">From magazine of standish,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-23" n="23">Drawn forth, 's more dreadful to the Dean,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-24" n="24">Than any sword we brandish.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-25" n="25"><lb/>My ink's my flash, my pen's my bolt;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-26" n="26">Whene'er I please to thunder,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-27" n="27">I'll make you tremble like a cold,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-S02215W1-line-28" n="28">And thus I'll keep you under.</l>
          </lg>
